Calling pocketknife's {{ModuleRegistrationHandle.unregister}} during spring context shutdown can cause a race with OSGi which leaves the bundle irrepairably broken an needing a server restart to recover. There is no need to unregister OSGi services - Felix (the OSGi framework) will do this when the bundle is stopped.

See [DESK-3588|https://jdog.jira-dev.com/browse/DESK-3588] for a similar issue and discussion.

